text: Welcome to 556 Yellowstone Drive in Grapevine! This charming brick home sits on a spacious corner lot and is surrounded by towering trees in the quiet, sought-after neighborhood of Autumn Hills. This property is zoned in the top-rated Grapevine Colleyville Independent School District. As you step into this delightful space, you will notice the sizeable living room with a vaulted ceiling and cozy fireplace. The dining room is full of light and open to both the kitchen and living space making it perfect for social events and family engagement. The ample sized kitchen boasts a farm sink, eye catching backsplash and upscale countertops polished off with crisp white cabinetry. Three bedrooms and two baths (second level) and a half bath (first level) complete this home. The primary bedroom is spacious, with double windows and natural light, as are the remaining bedrooms. Recent efforts in regard to this house include paint (2025), luxury vinyl flooring in bathrooms (2025), complete kitchen remodel including new appliances (2020), hot water tank (2019). The inviting backyard is perfect for a friendly bbq or a peaceful morning coffee. The backyard is shaded and boasts a rock retaining wall that includes spacious seating, great for entertaining. Close access to Dove Park Trail and Dove Waterpark allow for a leisurely stroll or weekend fun. Grapevine Lake is a short distance away, known for fishing, boating, skiing, paddleboarding, and the like or grab a burger on the water and listen to a local artist strum away. No water toys, no worries as everything you need can be rented on site. The property is minutes from highways 114 and 121. Nearby you will find a plethora of dining, shopping, and entertainment venues, as well as close proximity to DFW airport. Historic Downtown Grapevine is minutes away, as well. This home is a perfect combination of location, style, and convenience! Come and discover your future! Information to be verified by buyer or agent.

text: Live your best life in one of the most desirable homes in Historic Grapevine, located on a leafy residential street surrounded by exquisite examples of classic architecture. A truly walkable lifestyle just steps to Main Street, Hotel Vin, historic train station, and the dining, shopping and live music that make this charming city so unique. The historically significant home was built in 1940 by former Grapevine Mayor William Floyd Deacon. A thorough and award winning renovation was completed in 2015, preserving all of the history and charm and adding sophisticated modern livability. Sumptuous Bianco Venatino marble, Wolf commercial range, brilliant floor to ceiling windows, gleaming wood floors, and a spacious open floor plan make this home as functional as it is beautiful. Situated on a generous third-acre lot with a stunning 2021 pool, spa, outdoor kitchen and screened in porch, the outdoor living is a perfect backdrop for the Gatsby lifestyle with croquet and badminton on the expansive lawn, and homemade ice cream and rummy on the romantic screened in porch complete with fireplace. The dramatic dining room has walls of windows bringing the outdoors in for the most intimate and memorable dinner parties. When the sun goes down repair to the spacious rooftop terrace nestled in the tree tops. Join your neighbors on the lawn for the annual Christmas parade that goes right down the street. DFW Airport is just minutes away and the train to downtown Forth Worth is just a short stroll down the street. Glamorous marble-clad primary suite has soaking tub, dual vanities, oversized shower and walk in closet. Each of the three additional beds and baths are equally beautiful with their own unique style. Designer tile & lighting throughout. Energy efficient: Spray foam, dual tankless water heaters, dual zone ACs & LED throughout. This home has it all!

text: New construction!!! Welcome to The Grapevine Brownstones Phase 2! This a a limited opportunity to own a luxury Lock and Leave Residence in the heart of Grapevine across from Hotel Vin, steps from Historic Main St, Peace Plaza, Harvest Hall and The Grapevine REC. A short walk across Dallas Rd to the TEX Rail which will drop you at DFW Airport or Ft. Worth and the The Grapevine Vintage RR with special excursions including the Stockyards and the Christmas Train. This sought after Bordeaux Residence is one of the larger Residences with 4 stories, 3 bdrm, 3.5 bath, 2 car garage and a 4th floor rooftop patio. Extraordinary opportunity to own a stunning property at the end of a serene cul-de-sac, spanning 1.16 acres with breathtaking views of Grapevine Lake and direct access to Corp property. This remarkable estate that has never before graced the market, offers a unique blend of privacy, nature, and natural beauty. The street, lovingly named Labrador Bay by its developer in homage to her affection for Labrador dogs, sets the tone for a home that harmonizes with nature. Designed with the animal enthusiast in mind, this stately residence includes a dedicated 3-dog kennel and provides ample opportunities for wildlife and bird watching, as well as enjoying the serene sights of fish jumping in the lake. As you step inside, you're greeted by a beautifully open floorplan adorned with luxurious travertine floors. French doors lead to a covered patio, expanding the living space and offering panoramic, tree-lined views of the lake. The main floor is perfectly suited for entertaining, reflecting the owner's passion for hosting, and includes a convenient guest suite. The centrally located kitchen is complete with Thermador appliances, granite counters, and stately stained cabinets. Upstairs, the grand primary bedroom features a cozy sitting area and offers unparalleled views of the lake, ensuring a peaceful retreat. An additional bedroom completes the upper level, providing ample space for family or guests. A 3-car garage is discreetly located at the back of the home, preserving the property's elegant faade. This is a rare gem where comfort, style, and nature seamlessly blendready for you to create updates and cherished memories.

text: Welcome to 3052 Ridgeview Dr in Grapevine, a charming red-brick home shaded by towering pine trees in a quiet, sought-after neighborhood zoned to top-rated Glenhope Elementary in the highly desirable Grapevine-Colleyville ISD. This four-bedroom, three-bath home offers 2, 497 square feet of well-designed living space with fresh paint, new carpet, and a layout filled with natural light and flexible potential. A beautiful stairwell entry sets the tone, flanked by a formal dining room that could easily double as a home office. Multiple living areas provide the perfect balance of comfort and versatility, including a cozy family room with wood accents and a gas fireplace. The kitchen includes newer appliances and ample room for future updates. A bright breakfast area opens to a covered patio and low-maintenance backyardideal for enjoying morning coffee or relaxing in the evenings. Just minutes from Parr Park, Bear Creek Dog Park, and miles of scenic trails, this location is a haven for nature lovers and active lifestyles. The kitchen boasts granite countertops, island with sink, workstation, double ovens, microwave, and 4-burner gas cooktop. Utility room has pocket-door, sink, built-in ironing board and cabinets. Freshly painted interior and carpet installed in July 2025, as well as, updated secondary bathrooms. First-floor private primary suite showcases a tray ceiling, recessed lighting, and wood-look tile flooring that continues into the remodeled ensuite bath and closet. Spa-like bathroom features skylight, heated floors, soaking tub, frameless river rock shower, ceiling fan, and dual vanities while the walk-in closet includes a built-in ironing board and chest of drawers. Upstairs, three spacious bedrooms, one with cedar closet, another with pocket-door, Jack-and-Jill bath, an additional full bath, and a large game room with a raised ceiling, wet bar with bar seating, wine fridge & rack, and built-insplus a walk-out balcony overlooking the greenbelt. The 4th bedroom includes built-in cabinets and shelves with a desk area, making it ideal for a private office or guest suite. Additional highlights include an intercom system, central vacuum, 3-car garage configured with a 2-car bay and a separate single-car bay, all windows have a lifetime transferable warranty, plus a composition, hail-resistant Class IV roof (installed July 2025). The property backs to a serene green space and a tranquil creek.

text: Tucked at the end of a peaceful cul-de-sac, just a short walk from the shimmering shores of Lake Grapevine, stands a two-story home thats been loved, lived in, and carefully maintained since 1986. As you step through the front door, you're welcomed into a warm and inviting living room with soaring cathedral ceilings. A floor-to-ceiling brick fireplace anchors the space, enveloped by a wall of built-in bookcases. Overhead, a modern wagon wheel LED chandelier adds a touch of rustic elegance. The heart of the home is the kitchen, where morning coffee is shared at the eat-in nook and holiday meals are prepared for family and friends. Just beyond, theres a separate formal dining room, perfect for gatherings both big and small. Nearby, a spacious laundry room with extra storage and a convenient half bath make daily living easy. Upstairs, all three bedrooms are thoughtfully arranged for privacy and comfort. The primary suite offers its own en-suite bathroom, while two more bedrooms share a second full bath. Whether it's the laughter of children, the quiet hum of a home office, or the peace of a restful night's sleepthis upper level is ready for whatever life brings. Out back, a simple fenced yard and deck provide just enough space to enjoy the outdoorsno pool to maintain. Its the kind of yard where you can sip iced tea on a summer afternoon, grill on weekends, or let the dog run free. This all-electric home runs on city utilities, with upgraded security and fire alarm wiring in place (updated in early 2023). New carpet and luxury vinyl tile, installed in April 2023, Major items replaced since 2022 that include AC, Heat Pump, Hot Water Tank. Exterior professionally painted 4-24 with Sherwin Williams Paints and a 2019 Roof replacement add comfort and freshness throughout. So if you're looking for more than square footageif you're looking for a home with heart, history, and a future waiting to be writtenthis may be the one.

text: Just one block from Grapevines Historic Main Street, the iconic Lipscomb House perfectly blends timeless 1888 charm with the modern luxuries of a full-scale renovation. Completely reimagined in 2017 with no expense spared, it features a helical pier foundation, foam encapsulation, double pane windows, and all-new systems (HVAC, plumbing, electrical, roof, etc). In 2024, it was further upgraded with fresh interior and exterior paint, a whole-house Culligan water filtration system, upscale light fixtures, and a fully floored attic above the oversized detached garage for excellent storage. The backyard was reimagined with the shed relocated and old planters removed to maximize green space. Inside, you'll find refinished hardwood floors, bold design selections, and high-end finishes throughout. The chefs kitchen is a true showpiece with a 48 6-burner Thermador gas range with double ovens, built-in Thermador refrigerator, pellet ice maker, drink fridge, and leathered quartzite countertops, all opening to the living and dining areas for effortless entertaining. Just off the main space is a warm and inviting library with rolling ladder and fireplace, a dedicated office, and a charming mudroom. The primary suite includes a luxurious walk-in closet that connects directly to a spacious laundry room with sink and built-ins. Upstairs, youll find two large bedrooms with en suite baths, a cozy reading loft, and built-in dressers for extra storage and charm. Situated on a corner lot with a large circular driveway, multiple patios, and a pool-ready backyard. Need more space? Architectural plans for a fourth bedroom are already drawn and available. Just minutes from parks, the Botanical Gardens, and all the best that Grapevine has to offerthis is a rare opportunity to own one of the citys most special homes.

text: Welcome to The Grapevine Brownstones Phase 2! This new construction Monticello plan presents a limited opportunity to own a luxury Lock and Leave Residence in the heart of Grapevine across from Hotel Vin, steps from Historic Main St, Peace Plaza, Harvest Hall and The Grapevine REC. A short walk across Dallas Rd to the TEX Rail which will drop you at DFW Airport or Ft. Worth and the The Grapevine Vintage RR with special excursion including the Stockyards and the Christmas Train. This beautiful Residence is 4 stories with 3 bdrm, 3.5 bath, 2 car garage and the 4th floor rooftop patio. Amenities include 12 foot ceilings in the kitchen and living room, luxurious showers, a unique 2nd floor balcony off the kitchen, and faces one of only two courtyards in the community. Enjoy easy access to many of the special events Grapevine offers including Main St Days, Grapefest, and all that comes with being The Christmas Capital of Texas. Walking is easy with a 75 Walkscore and also quick access to highways, Southlake Town Square, and DFW Airport. This home will be built elevator ready and the buyer can choose to add after closing.

Quiet cul-de-sac in Prestigious Carroll ISD, this stunning V. Patrick Gray custom invites you into a lifestyle of elevated comfort & effortless indoor-outdoor resort-style living. Largest Lot in the Neighborhood. Soaring ceilings & wide-open areas flow seamlessly into the sprawling outdoor retreat. Double glass sliders, open to the expansive views & screened outdoor living space with outdoor fireplace, designed for family & entertaining! Enjoy grilling in the spacious outdoor kitchen w bar seating or relax in the sunken fire pit w travertine decking & lush native xeriscaping while listening to your favorite playlist on the outdoor sound system. Custom Library nook under floating stairs w a hidden shelf adds charm, flexible upstairs loft-style game room & 2 ensuite bedrooms provide space to grow & host. Spacious custom closet offers storage & organization. text: Dont miss this incredible 4-bedroom, 3-bathroom home on a cul-de-sac lot in an excellent Grapevine location just off 121, close to schools, shopping, dining, and DFW Airport. Inside, the home has been freshly painted and features warm oak-colored luxury vinyl flooring throughout the main level, complete with extra padding for added comfort. Two separate walk-out attic spaces offer added convenience. The backyard is truly a retreat, featuring lush landscaping, a covered patio, and a section of low-maintenance turfperfect for play, pets, or easy upkeep. Zoned to highly-rated Grapevine-Colleyville ISD schools. You don't want to miss this one!

text: Willow Wood Horse Farm is without a doubt one of the finest examples of modern architecture combined with an equestrian lifestyle on 9.753+/- acres. The residence was originally designed by Lou Simmons, who collaborated with Bob Sullivan on the project to help it come into completion. Situated in the heart of the Dallas-Fort Worth Metroplex, just minutes from Lake Grapevine, Southlake, and an easy commute to DFW International Airport, this property affords someone the ability to have all the comforts of the city, while living just slightly removed from it all. The main residence and equestrian facilities are immaculate and ready for the next generation of ownership. This property is a must have for the individual desiring to be close to the city but enjoy a more peaceful and country-like setting. Improvements: This custom designed home was completed in 2022 and is truly an example of elegance. The 4, 353 SF home demands attention as it sits on the highest point of the property. Hear the rumble of your tires on the cobble stone drive as you approach the house and take in the modern architectural masterpiece that awaits. Situated on either side of the main door of the home is a beautifully understated Koi pond that welcomes visitors before entering through the massive glass door and entry way. The home is constructed of insulated concrete form (ICF) with steal joists and a deck roof system. Walls and windows of the home provide superior thermal and sound insulation. After walking through the threshold, you will notice a grand view all the way through the living areas of the house, overlooking the 3, 000 SF IPE back deck, 80 ft long salt water swimming pool, through the pasture to the equestrian facilities. The welcoming views are complimented by a very warm and luxurious open-concept living space that combines the living room, kitchen, and dining areas. Custom quarter sawn walnut millworker can be found throughout the kitchen and living areas as well as the rest of the residence. The kitchen is ideal for the master chef with Gagneau appliances including a steam convection oven, a conventional convection oven, coffee machine, cooktop, dishwasher, separate paneled refrigerator and freezer units, as well as a warming drawer. Just off the kitchen is a half bath and a full butlers pantry with prep space and a full-size dishwasher. Each of the bedrooms has a unique and different view of the property. The primary bedroom features similar views to the main living area, a spacious walk-in closet, a bathroom with solid stone bath tub and wash basins by Piet Boone, and Donrbracht platinum plumbing fixtures. The two additional bedrooms have on suite bathrooms also with Donrbracht fixtures and excellent clothing storage for family or guests. All main rooms have Italian pocket door hardware with soft open/close features and are fully sealed with gaskets to aid in sound transfer between rooms when doors are closed. Journeying up and down the custom-built metal framed staircase is an artistic treat in itself. Going up the stairs to the second floor viewing area re-emphasizes the stunning views of the grounds and surrounding area, complete with a dishwasher, fridge/freezer/icemaker, a dumbwaiter, and floor to ceiling windows and doors that open to a covered porch and roof top IPE deck. The lower level of the home features an acoustically balanced theater with Dynaudio speakers and sound system designed by Ember Audio to provide a true movie theater experience from the comfort of your own home. The theatre is complete with a 250-bottle wine cooler, 8 ft concert walls, and a powder bath. All of which could also be used as a very nice storm cellar.

This home truly has it all!

Located just minutes to the boat launches at Grapevine Lake, this home can house your boat, toys, workshop, workout room, or the collection of cars of every hobbyist's dream! Check out the 4+ car barn with HVAC! With walkability to downtown Grapevine to the restaurants, shops, and wineries, you're sure to love this location! This historical home, known as the GE Hunt Home, was originally constructed in 1910 and rebuilt in 2016 through a meticulous renovation that preserved its soul while anchoring it in the now. Set on a lush half-acre lot filled with mature native trees, this home feels like a page out of Grapevines past with a future-proof foundation, literally built atop a modern steel pier-and-beam system. With over 4, 500 square feet under roof and 2, 780 square feet in the main home, the layout is as thoughtful as it is functional. Downstairs, the primary suite offers privacy and comfort with a spa-like ensuite bath, while a guest suite on the same floor provides hospitality with ease. A light-filled great room flows into the heart of the homea luxurious kitchen with Thermador appliances and era-inspired cabinetry and color, plus and a dining area designed for gathering. Upstairs, two additional bedrooms each feature full baths, accompanied by a second living area and an expansive office space that could double as a creative studio or library. The details tell the real story with preserved trimwork, hardwood floors, and antique-inspired fixtures which are all balanced by smart updates and energy-efficient systems. Outside, a 975 sq ft detached garage-workshop echoes the aesthetic of a classic Texas barn, offering functionality with curb appeal. And the porte-cochere near the mudroom and laundry isnt just a design feature, its a daily convenience, enhanced by the Generac generator, ready on demand to power the home. This is more than a historical homeits a legacy, lovingly restored and ready for its next chapter.
